Plot Summary for 
Good Morning, Vietnam (1987) 
A new Disc Jockey is shipped from Crete to Vietnam to bring humor to Armed Forces Radio. He turns the studio on it&#039;s ear and becomes wildly popular with the troops but runs afoul of the middle management who think he isn&#039;t G.I. enough. While he is off the air, he tries to meet Vietnamese especially girls, and begins to have brushes with the real war that never appears on the radio.
